The paper deals with the problem of dynamic spectrum access, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The authors formulate the interactions among the users as a non-cooperative game, which falls under game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses multi-agent learning algorithms, which is a topic related to networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes an approximated utility function, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.MA).
